<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[98,749,578,835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<bibRefCitation author="GRENIER &amp; GODRON" box="[136,425,682,706]" firstAuthor="GRENIER" journalOrPublisher="Mem. Soc. Emul. Doubs" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="12 - 15" part="6" refId="ref2508" refString="GRENIER, J. C. M. &amp; D. A. GODRON (1855). Notices botaniques sur quelques plantes des genres Fritillaria, Asphodelus et Melica. Mem. Soc. Emul. Doubs ser. 2, 6: 12 - 15." title="Notices botaniques sur quelques plantes des genres Fritillaria, Asphodelus et Melica" type="journal article" year="1855">GRENIER &amp; GODRON (1855)</bibRefCitation>
quote several syntypes for this taxon. From the localities cited in the protologue, we traced, in P and K, specimens that can be considered as original material. Among these we choose the most well-developed and well-presented as lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[98,749,851,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[136,376,851,875]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Taxonomic discussion</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[412,643,851,875]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiformis">
<emphasis box="[412,643,851,875]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Fritillaria tubiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was long confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="L." box="[258,421,883,907]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis box="[258,390,883,907]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. meleagris</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
(i.e., 
<bibRefCitation author="BERTOLONI" box="[484,669,883,907]" firstAuthor="BERTOLONI" journalOrPublisher="Bologna." pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="73 - 76" part="4" refId="ref2468" refString="BERTOLONI, A. (1839). Fl. Italiana 4: 73 - 76. Bologna." title="Fl. Italiana" type="journal article" year="1839">BERTOLONI, 1839</bibRefCitation>
), but it is clearly distinct from all other species from West Europe 
<bibRefCitation author="GRENIER, J. C. M. &amp; D. A. GODRON" box="[126,383,947,971]" journalOrPublisher="Mem. Soc. Emul. Doubs" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="12 - 15" part="6" refId="ref2508" refString="GRENIER, J. C. M. &amp; D. A. GODRON (1855). Notices botaniques sur quelques plantes des genres Fritillaria, Asphodelus et Melica. Mem. Soc. Emul. Doubs ser. 2, 6: 12 - 15." title="Notices botaniques sur quelques plantes des genres Fritillaria, Asphodelus et Melica" type="journal article" year="1855">RENIER &amp; GODRON, 1855</bibRefCitation>
). On the other hand, it seems close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Willd." authorityName="Willd." box="[126,312,980,1004]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis box="[126,237,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. latifolia</emphasis>
Willd.
</taxonomicName>
, widespread from Caucasus to N Turkey 
<bibRefCitation author="RIX, E. M." box="[125,215,1012,1036]" journalOrPublisher="The Fritillaria Group of the Alpine Garden Society, United Kingdom" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" refId="ref2775" refString="RIX, E. M. (2001). Fritillaria. A revised classification. The Fritillaria Group of the Alpine Garden Society, United Kingdom." title="Fritillaria. A revised classification" type="book" year="2001">IX, 2001</bibRefCitation>
), from which it differs in having glaucous leaves (vs. shiny green) and shorter style branches. Among the taxa usually synonymized with 
<emphasis box="[384,526,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName box="[384,519,1076,1100]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiformis">F. tubiformis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
two seem to deserve special attention (
<taxonomicName authority="Planch." authorityName="Planch." box="[298,701,1108,1132]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="delphinensis" variety="burnatii">
<emphasis box="[298,465,1108,1132]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. delphinensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[521,611,1108,1132]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">burnatii</emphasis>
Planch.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Planch." authorityName="Planch." box="[98,523,1141,1165]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" form="moggridgei" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="delphinensis">
<emphasis box="[98,268,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. delphinensis</emphasis>
f. 
<emphasis box="[302,431,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">moggridgei</emphasis>
Planch.
</taxonomicName>
), while others have doubtful taxonomic value (i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="Rouy" authorityName="Rouy" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="delphinensis" variety="reverchonii">
<emphasis box="[425,580,1173,1197]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. delphinensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[630,748,1173,1197]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">reverchonii</emphasis>
Rouy
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="ROUY" box="[171,297,1205,1229]" firstAuthor="ROUY" journalOrPublisher="Paris." pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="401 - 405" part="12" refId="ref2803" refString="ROUY, G. (1910). Fl. France 12: 401 - 405. Paris." title="Fl. France" type="journal article" year="1910">ROUY, 1910</bibRefCitation>
). Similarly to what was done recently with the 
<taxonomicName authority="W. D. J. Koch" authorityName="W. D. J. Koch" box="[139,425,1237,1261]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[139,263,1237,1261]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. montana</emphasis>
W. D. J. Koch
</taxonomicName>
complex (
<bibRefCitation author="BARTOLUCCI" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="BARTOLUCCI" journalOrPublisher="Pl. Biosyst." pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="516 - 527" part="143" refId="ref2407" refString="BARTOLUCCI, F., K. F. CAPARELLI &amp; L. PERUZZI (2009). A biometric study of Fritillaria montana Hoppe ex W. D. J. Koch s. l. (Liliaceae) shows a single polymorphic species, with no infraspecific taxa. Pl. Biosyst. 143: 516 - 527." title="A biometric study of Fritillaria montana Hoppe ex W. D. J. Koch s. l. (Liliaceae) shows a single polymorphic species, with no infraspecific taxa" type="journal article" year="2009">BARTOLUCCI &amp; al., 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="PERUZZI" box="[168,380,1269,1293]" etAl="&amp; al." firstAuthor="PERUZZI" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="237 - 244" part="64" refId="ref2635" refString="PERUZZI, L., K. F. CAPARELLI &amp; F. BARTOLUCCI (2009). Fritillaria messanensis subsp. neglecta (Parl.) Nyman, a fourth subspecies within Fritillaria messanensis (Liliaceae) from NW Balkans. Candollea 64: 237 - 244." title="Fritillaria messanensis subsp. neglecta (Parl.) Nyman, a fourth subspecies within Fritillaria messanensis (Liliaceae) from NW Balkans" type="journal article" year="2009">PERUZZI &amp; al., 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="PERUZZI &amp; BARTOLUCCI" box="[396,714,1269,1293]" firstAuthor="PERUZZI" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" pagination="133 - 142" part="64" refId="ref2600" refString="PERUZZI, L. &amp; F. BARTOLUCCI (2009). Typification of the names within Fritillaria montana complex (Liliaceae) from central Mediterranean area. Candollea 64: 133 - 142." title="Typification of the names within Fritillaria montana complex (Liliaceae) from central Mediterranean area" type="journal article" year="2009">PERUZZI &amp; BARTOLUCCI, 2009</bibRefCitation>
), a biosystematic study is in progress about the 
<taxonomicName authority="L." box="[583,749,1302,1326]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis box="[583,717,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. meleagris</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
complex (
<taxonomicName box="[209,345,1334,1358]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="meleagris">
<emphasis box="[209,345,1334,1358]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[353,385,1334,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[439,580,1334,1358]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="tubiformis">
<emphasis box="[439,580,1334,1358]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">F. tubiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[587,620,1334,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), aiming to clarify the relationships among the taxa and their distribution.
</paragraph>
